-- U.S. administration says midday HealthCare.gov glitch resolved 
-- By David Morgan
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 01:43PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, March 31 (Reuters) - The Obama administration said on Monday that it has resolved a glitch affecting HealthCare.gov that temporarily prevented new users from accessing application and enrollment tools around midday, as website traffic volumes surged hours before a midnight deadline to enroll in private health insurance.        (Reporting by David Morgan; Editing by Meredith Mazzilli)  ((david.morgan@thomsonreuters.com)(+1)(202)(898 8326)(twitter.com/dmorganreuters)(Reuters Messaging: david.morgan.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: USA HEALTHCARE/GLITCH

